Bangladesh public figure's impressions of Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 14 (KCNA) -- Badal Khan, general secretary of the National Workers' Federation of Bangladesh, referring to his impressions of Korea, stressed that all the enemies' slanders and moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK could never break the indomitable faith and will of the Korean people to advance along the road of socialism chosen by themselves under the leadership of the great Kim Jong Il.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is the brilliant fruition of the army-first politics of Kim Jong Il that socialism of Korea has won victory after victory without a moment's stagnation and standstill. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Under his army-first politics the Korean people have wrought astonishing miracles one after another, breaking through the difficulties by themselves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The solidity and invincibility of Korean-style socialism lies in the fact that it is people-centred socialism which puts forward the people as the genuine master of society and makes all social things serve the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean people are filled with the desire to carry forward the revolutionary cause of Juche, which was pioneered by the respected Kim Il Sung, to the end under the leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Jong Il is the great defender of the socialist cause as well as the prominent leader of the age of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   I am firmly convinced that the Korean people will defend the best socialism of Korean style in the world and build a rich and prosperous powerful nation without fail, upholding his idea and leadership.

Celebrated works newly exhibited 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 14 (KCNA) -- Celebrated works of the  President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il are newly exhibited at the hall for the exhibition of works on the Juche idea.   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Exhibited works include "Complete Collection of Kim Il Sung's Works" vols. 24, 25 and 26 and a collection of Kim Jong Il's works and their works which were translated into over 10 foreign languages and published in book form in 20 countries for the last 3 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Carried in the "Complete Collection of Kim Il Sung's Works" vols. 24, 25 and 26 are the works published from June Juche 48 (1959) to March Juche 50 (1961), and in the collection of Kim Jong Il's works are the works published from February Juche 81 (1992) to June Juche 83 (1994). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Volumes 24, 25 and 26 of the "Complete Collection of Kim Il Sung's Works" contain  works "On Some Immediate Tasks In Socialist Economic  Construction," "Chollima Riders Are Heroes of Our Age and Red Warriors of the Party" and "On Strengthening Political Work In the People's Army."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The collection of Kim Jong Il's works contains works "On Fundamentals of  Revolutionary Party Building," "Abuses of Socialism Are Intolerable" and "On Establishing the Social Spirit of Strengthening the People's Army and Giving Importance To the Military."

Annual meeting of Guyana committee 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 14 (KCNA) -- An annual meeting of the Guyana Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification was held on January 7 in Georgetown. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The meeting reviewed the activities of the committee last year and decided an action program this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The meeting also discussed measures for conducting energetic solidarity activities to support the  reunification of Korea on the occasion of the birthday of General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A statement supporting the joint new year editorial was adopted after speeches were made at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The statement extended support and solidarity to the Korean people in their struggle for the independent and peaceful reunification of the country and expressed the belief  that Korea would surely be reunified in the near future in accordance with the three principles of national reunification, the ten-point program of the great unity of the whole nation and the proposal for founding the Democratic Confederal Republic of Koryo.

U.S.-Japan moves for military cooperation denounced 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 14 (KCNA) -- Some time ago, a foreign policy aide to bush, a republican candidate for the presidency of the United States, said that Japan, together with the U.S. and its allies, should be more responsible for security in East Asia, adding Japan's armed forces should be closely coordinated with the U.S. troops to support the latter in Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Commenting on his argument, Minju Joson today says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This betrays once again the unchanged intention of the United States to use Japan as a shock brigade for the implementation of its policy of hostility toward Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The U.S. final aim is to stifle the DPRK by force of arms and hold supremacy over East Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It intends to make full use of geographical features and military potentials of Japan and its militaristic ambition for reinvasion to realize its Asia strategy without difficulty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   What cannot be overlooked is that Japan has shown affirmative response to such intention and military demand of the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The director general of the Japan Defense Agency flew to the United States a few days ago to have a war confab with American warhawks for aggression on the DPRK. And he discussed with them the issue of acquiring high-tech warships equipped with necessary electronic information devices. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is the intention of the Japanese reactionaries to turn the "Self-Defense Forces" into an army equipped with the latest war equipment and realize their design for overseas expansion, with the backing of the U.S.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The United States should know that its policy of strength to stifle the DPRK will never bring good results to it and the Japanese reactionaries should stop such foolish moves hastening their own destruction.

Gigantic waterway project progresses apace 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 14 (KCNA) -- The Kaechon Lake Thaesong waterway project is in full gear in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This is a gigantic nature-harnessing project aimed at constructing a lock gate on the Taedong River flowing through the western area of the country to divert scores of tons of water per second and store hundreds of millions of cubic meters of water in reservoirs found in areas from several cities and counties of South Phyongan Province to Lake Thaesong. It is, in fact, the largest project in the nation's history of irrigation as it involves digging of some 160 km-long waterway, construction of scores of water tunnels and many structures, removal of at least 15 million cubic metres of earth, tamping of more than 400,000 cubic metres of concrete and paving of dikes with over 110,000 square metres of stones. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The DPRK intends to complete this project, one of the major construction objects, in a brief span of time through a movement involving the entire party and army and all the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The builders are hard pressed for everything and the conditions remain difficult. But, they are accelerating the project from the outset of the year, breaking through bottlenecks and difficulties, full of confidence and optimism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The completion of the project would make it possible to supply a sufficient amount of water from the taedong river to 99,000 hectares of farmland in 15 cities, counties and districts in South Phyongan Province, Pyongyang and Nampho under any conditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Fed with water of the river taedong, more than 20 reservoirs will no longer need the operation of the existing 380-odd water pumping stations and more than 530 water pumps. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A sufficient supply of industrial and drinking water to Nampho and large and small reservoirs always full of water would make the landscape of the country more beautiful and greatly help develop fish farming and improve the standard of people's living.

Worker-peasant red guards 41 years old 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 14 (KCNA) -- Today the worker-peasant red guards celebrates its foundation day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The civilian revolutionary armed forces of the DPRK was founded on January 14, 1959. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is at the core of the civilian armed forces of the DPRK, which is very instrumental in the all-people, nationwide defense system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It has grown in strength to carry out any operation in cooperation with the Korean People's Army and defeat imperialist aggressors by itself. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A unitary organizational and commanding system has been established in all regions and units across the country to quickly react to any unexpected situation. Towns, rural villages and other places have been built into a fortress strong enough to repel any surprise attack and strike by the enemy. The DPRK has turned into an impregnable fortress reminiscent of a guerrilla base built in Xiaowangqing in the period of the anti-Japanese armed struggle led by the President Kim Il Sung. In those days the people in the guerrilla base and guerrillas turned out to defend the base from the unabated "punitive operations" of the Japanese imperialists who outnumbered them scores of times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Long ago, General Secretary Kim Jong Il said it was a plan of the President and his own resolution to equip all the people with arms, turn the whole country into an impregnable fortress like the base in Xiaowangqing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The spirit displayed in the defence of the Xiaowangqing base has been conveyed down through generations in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It was in that spirit that the people's army soldiers and people defended height 1211 during the last Korean War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The recently-published joint new year editorial calls upon all the people to push ahead with production and construction, a rifle in one hand and a hammer or sickle in the other, keeping an alert and standing posture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Members of the worker-peasant red guards defend their hometowns and working places in full combat readiness to cope with new war moves of the U.S. and their stooges, which have recently gotten all the more pronounced.
